Washington D.C. Commuters 2020

Source: R/commuters.R
commuters.Rd

Washington D.C. inbound and outbound commuters by county 2020

Usage

commuters

Format

A data frame with 97 rows and 10 columns

one

one

Source

https://www.census.gov/data/tables/2020/demo/metro-micro/commuting-flows-2020.html Data was created by the U.S. government and is not subject to copyright in the United States pursuant to 17 U.S.C. § 105.

Details

From the U.S. Census Bureau: "The American Community Survey (ACS) asks respondents about their primary workplace location. When information about workers’ residence location and workplace location are coupled, a commuting flow is generated. The origin-destination flow format informs our understanding of interconnectedness between communities, including the interchange of people, goods, and services." For additional information, see the page on commuter data.

References

U.S. Census Bureau, 2016-2020 5-Year ACS Commuting Flows (2020) last accessed October 24, 2024.
